author: Frank Torres
title: Marsha Blackburn to headline GOP Women’s Convention in Orlando
text:
Pinterest 0 
Marsha Blackburn (R-TN-7) will be the keynote speaker at the Florida Federation of Republican Women convention this Saturday night in Orlando. 
Blackburn was elected to Congress in 2002 and subsequently. She is nationally recognized mentor to GOP women seeking election to office. 
“Marsha Blackburn does not mince words. She is a woman on a mission. Florida women join her on that mission and are determined to campaign, raise funds and elect more women on the local, state and national level,” said Cynthia Henderson , president of the Florida Federation of Republican Women. 
Blackburn is a media regular and is one of the most outspoken women in the country regarding the fight against Planned Parenthood, higher taxes, government waste and Hillary Clinton . Rep. Marsha Blackburn
